&lt;p&gt;NUPAS (National Unplanned Pregnancy Advisory Services) is one of the three independent sector Abortion Care providers in the UK&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for dynamic, enthusiastic and motivated individuals to join our clinical team as consultation doctors. This is an excellent opportunity to increase your knowledge and skills in Abortion care, Sexual Health and Contraception provision in the UK.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The job will include consultations (pre and post abortion) inclusive of contraception provision, prescriptions and compliance with the legal abortion framework. You shall contribute to evaluation/audit in a clinical standard setting and have a commitment to lifelong learning. You shall have an approach that encourages and enables continuous personal and service improvement. Ultrasound scanning capability is desirable but not compulsory.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Consultation doctors are currently based at Manchester and Stockport but travel to other parts of the country will be required on an occasional basis. The successful candidate will be providing both face to face consultations as well as telemedicine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is for 24 hours per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Basic salary will be £86,364.00 pro rata per annum.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact n.ghosh@nhs.net or aaron.flaherty@nupas.co.uk&lt;/p&gt;
